article.headline: Rhode Island 77, Providence 60
article.story: SOUTH KINGSTOWN, R.I. (AP) -- Will Daniels had 18 points and Jimmy Baron added 17 to lead Rhode Island in a 77-60 win over Providence on Tuesday night. Kahiem Seawright also had 13 points and 10 rebounds for the 9-1 Rams. Providence, 5-2, holds a 66-53 edge in the 118-game series between the state rivals. The Friars, shooting a season-low 30.4 percent from the floor, had 12 points from Brian Williams and 11 points each from Jonathan Kale and Dwain Williams. Rhode Island led 33-28 at the half, and increased its advantage to 18 points after a 13-1 run midway through the second half. The Friars fell behind 14-7 early in the game after a stretch of 3:28 in which they failed to make a field goal attempt. Jeff Xavier gave Providence its biggest lead, 24-21, late in the first half with two 3-pointers moments apart.
